    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="grc" resp="#JP">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/>Βέττιος Μαύ
                    <lb n="2" break="no"/>ρικος <choice><reg>ἐτῶν</reg><orig>ἐτρῶν</orig></choice>
                    <lb n="3"/><num value="10">ι</num> ἔζησεν δὲ τὸ
                    <lb n="4" break="no"/>ν ἑαυτοῦ <choice><orig>βείο<supplied reason="lost">ν</supplied></orig><reg>βίο<supplied reason="lost">ν</supplied></reg></choice>
                    <lb n="5"/>κῖτε ἐν τούτ
                    <lb n="6" break="no"/>ῳ τῷ τύ<hi rend="reversed">ν</hi>βῳ
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app><note>Text based upon the engraving prepared by Castelli, Principe di Torremuzza</note></app>
                    <app loc="line 3"><note>Kaibel proposes Π for the age, but it is not clear on what basis; as Castelli observes, iota is clear; Muratori reported Κ</note></app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP">
                <p>Bettios Maurikos lived his own life for 10 years, he lies in this tomb</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Muratori's edition on three lines is condemned by Castelli, Principe di Torremuzza, and the latter's engraving forms the basis for the current edition. The inscription was transferred to the Museum of San Martino, but does not seem to have passed from there to the Palermo museum and is now lost. </p>
            </div>
